---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import NewsletterSignup from '../../components/NewsletterSignup.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="BYD Canada Pre-order Info — BYD Finder"
  description="How and when to pre-order a BYD in Canada. Reservation timelines, deposit amounts, dealer network updates."
>
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 md:px-6 py-12 md:py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight leading-tight text-[var(--color-ink)]">
      Pre-ordering a BYD in Canada
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-[var(--color-ink-soft)]">
      Everything we know about the Canadian pre-order and reservation process &mdash;
      updated as BYD announces details.
    </p>

    <div class="prose-article mt-8">
      <h2>Current status (April 2026)</h2>
      <p>
        BYD has not yet opened official pre-orders in Canada, but preparations
        are well underway. In March 2026, BYD hired Dealer Solutions Mergers &amp;
        Acquisitions (Markham, Ontario) to scout retail locations, with initial
        discussions focused on three Greater Toronto Area sites. The company
        is targeting up to 20 Canadian dealerships within its first year of
        operations.
      </p>
      <p>
        BYD is the only Chinese passenger-vehicle manufacturer currently
        registered with Transport Canada's Appendix G preclearance registry &mdash;
        the furthest along of any Chinese EV maker on the regulatory path to
        Canadian sales.
      </p>

      <h2>Expected timeline</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Mid-2026:</strong> demo units expected to arrive at early Toronto dealerships</li>
        <li><strong>Late 2026:</strong> limited retail availability projected</li>
        <li><strong>2027:</strong> expansion to Vancouver, Montreal, Calgary and beyond</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        BYD has signalled that four models are being readied for the Canadian
        market, though the specific lineup has not been confirmed publicly.
      </p>

      <h2>What to expect from pre-orders</h2>
      <p>
        Based on BYD's rollouts in other markets, reservations typically open
        with a refundable deposit (commonly $500&ndash;$1,000) ahead of dealer
        availability. Expect:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>An online reservation portal at BYD's Canadian site</li>
        <li>Refundable deposit to hold a spot in the delivery queue</li>
        <li>Model and trim selection lockable closer to delivery</li>
        <li>Delivery priority by deposit date</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Tariff context</h2>
      <p>
        Canada's negotiated 6.1% duty on Chinese EVs is dramatically lower than
        the 100% U.S. tariff, making Canada one of the most favorable developed
        markets for BYD's North American push. This is the primary reason BYD
        has moved so aggressively on Canadian retail.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12">
      <NewsletterSignup
        variant="hero"
        heading="First to know when pre-orders open"
        subheading="One email the moment BYD Canada opens reservations. No spam."
      />
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
